cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the usage of cognitive radio devices within the service area of TV broadcast stations, which involves networking and communication aspects. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the utilization of TV receiver information to increase cognitive white space spectrum, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the protection of TV broadcast stations service area and avoiding harmful interference to TV receivers, which involves security and cryptography aspects. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of cognitive radio on TV receivers, which involves multimedia aspects. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the simulation-based approach to analyze the impact of cognitive radio on TV receivers, which involves systems and control aspects.
